2.40	Cruiser_Mk_III	Cruiser Mk III	The Tank, Cruiser, Mk III was a British cruiser tank of the Second World War. It was the first British cruiser tank to use the Christie suspension system which gave higher speeds and better cross-country performance, previous models of cruiser tanks having used triple wheeled bogie suspension.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b2/IWM-KID-358-Cruiser-MkIII.jpg/300px-IWM-KID-358-Cruiser-MkIII.jpg
